## TL;DR: What Every Cushion Cut Engagement Ring Buyer Must Know First

A cushion cut diamond engagement ring pairs one of the most popular fancy shapes with the widest range of setting options available in any diamond shape — and that width is exactly the problem. The cushion's large, open table exposes the stone's true character more directly than a round brilliant does. Choose the right setting and the cushion looks magnificent. Choose the wrong one and the same certified stone looks smaller, warmer, and less impressive than its price tag suggests.

**Contrarian Truth — The Pillow Premium:** Most buyers assume cushion cut is the budget alternative to more "prestigious" shapes. It is not. At the same carat weight and grade, a cushion cut diamond costs 8–15% more than a princess cut and sits within 5–10% of oval pricing. The cushion premium is real, structural, and almost universally surprising to first-time buyers.

