## What Is a Cushion Cut Diamond Engagement Ring?

A cushion cut diamond engagement ring is an engagement ring centred on a cushion modified brilliant or cushion brilliant diamond — a square-to-rectangular fancy shape with softly curved, pillow-like corners and a brilliant-cut facet arrangement that produces strong sparkle without the geometric sharpness of a princess cut or the perfect symmetry of a round. GIA classifies cushion as a fancy shape and issues no cut grade; the buyer must evaluate proportions, video, and setting compatibility independently.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. Cushion cut is the third most popular engagement ring shape globally in {{year}}, behind round brilliant and oval, and ahead of princess — a reversal of where the market stood a decade ago. The cushion's rise mirrors the broader shift toward vintage-influenced, soft-edged aesthetics over the geometric precision that dominated engagement ring buying in the 2000s and early 2010s.

What makes the cushion cut engagement ring uniquely demanding to buy is exactly what makes it beautiful: the large, open table and soft corner geometry create a face that is visually generous but unforgiving of poor setting choices. A round brilliant hides minor setting flaws behind its optical density. A cushion does not.

This guide covers every setting type, every metal option, the named concepts that separate informed buyers from disappointed ones, complete live price data from Blue Nile, and the exact builds that deliver maximum value at each budget tier.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

